HEADWORD: Perseus
<hw>Per"se*us</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>prop. n.</pos> <ety>[L., from Gr. <grk>Persey`s</grk>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Class. Myth.)</fld> <def>A Grecian legendary hero, son of Jupiter and Dana⟦eum⟧, who slew the Gorgon Medusa.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Astron.)</fld> <def>A consellation of the northern hemisphere, near Taurus and Cassiopea. It contains a star cluster visible to the naked eye as a nebula.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Persever</ent>⟦br⟧
